   "policy_definition": "Insufficient grounded evidence in the provided documents to define \"when a pharmacy must bill Medicaid before billing Medicare\" for policy documents. The newest policy document, \"New York State Medicaid Update May 2023 Volume 39 Number 10\" effective 2023-05-01, provides general FFS billing instructions, such as entering a value of \"5\" in the Prescription Origin Code field, but does not specify the order of billing relative to Medicare [New York State Medicaid Update May 2023 Volume 39 Number 10:10, 11 — 2023-05-01]. Other policy documents discuss auto-refill policies or immunization billing, also without addressing the billing order between Medicaid and Medicare [New York State Medicaid Update May 2021 Volume 37 Number 6:5 — 2021-05-01], [New York State Medicaid Update September 2022 Volume 38 Number 10:3 — 2022-09-01].",
